00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:27,892
His life is to be understood in a very, very deep sense.

476
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:29,892

477
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:32,892
But if you are like a journalist, you can say,

478
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:40,892
“Why did He crucify Himself? If He was God why did He get crucified?”

479
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:41,892

480
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:44,892
Now the question is why He got crucified,

481
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:49,892
is how to tell these journalists who don’t know anything about chakras.

482
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:58,892
Because it was the era or the time of tapasya, of sacrifice, and so

483
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:10,892
then all these three persons - Buddha, Mahavira and Christ - went into complete renunciation.

484
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:13,892

485
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:19,892
They led a life of a great tapasvis.

486
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:25,892
They did it for us, not for themselves. They didn’t need it.

487
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:32,892
They didn’t want it; but they had do it to cleanse us,

488
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:43,892
to give us a proper Medha as they call it this Ekadesha Rudras,

489
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:46,892
you see, to be cleared out;

490
00:45:47,000 --> 00:45:53,892
and they have sacrificed their lives, they have sacrificed all the pleasures of life.

491
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:59,892
For them it was not a sacrifice, it is just a kind of a life they wanted to have.

492
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:07,892
For such people there’s no question of sacrifice, but is a question of doing something

493
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:14,892
that would help to open the chakras of the people in the future.

494
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:17,892
Without them we could not have worked out Sahaja Yoga.

495
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:27,892
It was essential for these people to cleanse for us these three chakras,

496
00:46:28,000 --> 00:46:32,892
part of the one Chakra of Christ.

497
00:46:33,000 --> 00:46:34,892

498
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:45,892
All this they have worked out, and that's why today Sahaja Yoga is so beautifully created,

499
00:46:46,000 --> 00:46:52,892
so beautifully spreading, is working out. We have to thank them very much.

500
00:46:53,000 --> 00:46:55,892
Of course all other incarnations also have helped,

501
00:46:56,000 --> 00:47:01,892
you can see, Vishuddhi, then also heart, and all these - right heart, left heart -

502
00:47:02,000 --> 00:47:06,892
all these angels as they are called in the Bible,

503
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:09,892
have helped us to cross over.

504
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:14,892
All these incarnations are responsible in our evolutionary process

505
00:47:15,000 --> 00:47:18,892
to create these ladders for us to move.

506
00:47:19,000 --> 00:47:20,892

507
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:28,892
So, ultimately you reach the state of Tapah

508
00:47:29,000 --> 00:47:35,892
on the sixth center and then in the state of truth, Satya.

509
00:47:36,000 --> 00:47:41,892
Then the truth comes to you through Sahaja Yoga, in the brain,

510
00:47:42,000 --> 00:47:46,892
in the limbic area when the Kundalini enters, She puts light there,

511
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:51,892
She creates enlightened personalities

512
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:57,892
and then She joins this all-pervading power of divine love,

513
00:47:58,000 --> 00:48:06,892
and with this divine love you are completely changed and transformed.

514
00:48:07,000 --> 00:48:08,892

515
00:48:09,000 --> 00:48:17,892
So their contribution to the ascent of human beings has been great,

516
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:20,892
and that of Christ has been the greatest.

517
00:48:21,000 --> 00:48:26,892
And when we say we have to follow Christ,

518
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:32,892
we should try to see how much detachment we have.

519
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:34,892

520
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:39,892
They say His brothers and sisters, or somebody came to see Him.

521
00:48:40,000 --> 00:48:44,892
They say He had brothers. So He said, “Who are My brothers?

522
00:48:45,000 --> 00:48:48,892
These are My brothers, these are My relations.”

523
00:48:49,000 --> 00:48:54,892
Gyaneshwara said the same thing, that "They will become your relations

524
00:48:55,000 --> 00:49:00,892
[Marathi, sounds like SO ERIKO, TE CHEEZ SO ERIKO TE]. They will be your relations,

525
00:49:01,000 --> 00:49:06,892
they'll be your brothers and sisters, and not those who are not enlightened.

526
00:49:07,000 --> 00:49:09,892
They are not your relations because they don’t understand you.

527
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:17,892
They don’t have entry into the Kingdom of God,

528
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:30,892
so they are not your relations." In His lifetime, He led a life of a person who was very simple.

529
00:49:31,000 --> 00:49:33,892
Didn’t bother about clothes or anything.

530
00:49:34,000 --> 00:49:37,892
All the conditioning of the worldly things were not His,

531
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:44,892
but He was not shameless type of a person who would accept any kind of a nudity and this and that.

532
00:49:45,000 --> 00:49:50,892
Even about Mahavira there’s a big misconcept.

533
00:49:51,000 --> 00:49:59,892
He was once praying in a garden where there were lots of bushes, we call them kunjas,

534
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:06,892
and in the bush His cloth, which was only one cloth He was putting on, was caught up.

535
00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:09,892
So He cut half of it and was covering Himself.

536
00:50:10,000 --> 00:50:17,892
Shri Krishna went to test Him, and He said that “I have nothing, I am just nude,

537
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:24,892
so why don’t you give Me your cloth? Because, after all, You are a king.”

538
00:50:25,000 --> 00:50:34,892
So He took out his cloth and gave it to Shri Krishna, and got some leaves to cover Himself

539
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:38,892
and He was in His own garden, and went into His own palace.

540
00:50:39,000 --> 00:50:46,892
Now, if you see the Jains, they make everything so horrible and insult Him all the time.

541
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:54,892
Most of the people who follow all these great incarnations really all the time insult them.

542
00:50:55,000 --> 00:50:56,892

543
00:50:57,000 --> 00:51:01,892
They don’t follow, they insult, and by their behavior, you see,

544
00:51:02,000 --> 00:51:06,892
we form such a bad opinion of all these people.

545
00:51:07,000 --> 00:51:07,892

546
00:51:08,000 --> 00:51:11,892
I met one gentleman in Chicago. It was very cold.

547
00:51:12,000 --> 00:51:15,892
He was the head of the Hare Rama Hare Krishna.

548
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:21,892
He was wearing a dhoti which was so thin, and he was shaking before Me.

549
00:51:22,000 --> 00:51:25,892
I said, “What’s the matter?”

550
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:27,892
He said, “I’m feeling very cold.”

551
00:51:28,000 --> 00:51:29,892
I said, “Why are you wearing this dhoti?”

552
00:51:30,000 --> 00:51:34,892
He said, “My guru has told me if you wear a dhoti you will go to heaven.”

553
00:51:35,000 --> 00:51:40,892
I said, “Really? In India eighty percent people wear nothing but dhotis,

554
00:51:41,000 --> 00:51:43,892
are they all going to go to heaven? And many must have gone already,

555
00:51:44,000 --> 00:51:47,892
so where will you be?” Didn’t like it.

556
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:53,892
Then I said, "Why you shaved your hair and put this …”we call it shindi, or in Hindi, bhodi.

557
00:51:54,000 --> 00:51:58,892
I don’t know what you call - pig’s tail here, pig’s tail?

558
00:51:59,000 --> 00:52:01,892
So he says, “It is because my guru told me

559
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:07,892
that I must shave my head and have this kind of a thing.” So I think perhaps,

560
00:52:08,000 --> 00:52:13,892
maybe he will be tied to some rope and pulled in the heaven or something,

561
00:52:14,000 --> 00:52:15,892

562
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:27,892
I said. Kabira has said - Kabira was one of them who has tried to slash out all your conditioning.

563
00:52:28,000 --> 00:52:32,892
He said, “By shaving your head, if you are going to go to heaven,

564
00:52:33,000 --> 00:52:35,892

565
00:52:36,000 --> 00:52:44,892
so what about the lamb which is shaved twice a year?

566
00:52:45,000 --> 00:52:48,892
He’ll be there earlier than you.”

567
00:52:49,000 --> 00:52:50,892
It’s a fact, it's so, such stupid things.

568
00:52:51,000 --> 00:52:56,892
And there are Jain sadhus who will remain absolutely nude and will pull their hair.

569
00:52:57,000 --> 00:53:04,892
Now by law they are allowed to go nude on the street, you know, insulting everyone.

570
00:53:05,000 --> 00:53:09,892
All such stupid things are happening in the name of religion -

571
00:53:10,000 --> 00:53:13,892
that, too, of Buddha, Mahavira, and Christ.

572
00:53:14,000 --> 00:53:15,892

573
00:53:16,000 --> 00:53:23,892
They are the Ones who are trying to pull us away from rationality,

574
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:26,892
because you have to cross this.

575
00:53:27,000 --> 00:53:36,892
All your limitations are because of this thinking, conditioning.

576
00:53:37,000 --> 00:53:43,892
We have to go beyond because by thinking, what do we do?

577
00:53:44,000 --> 00:53:48,892
We move in a linear way and then there’s no truth in it,

578
00:53:49,000 --> 00:53:54,892
so the whole thing comes back, boomerangs, and you are finished.

579
00:53:55,000 --> 00:53:59,892
We have to go beyond this mind; must understand this point is.

580
00:54:00,000 --> 00:54:05,892
Christ has done this so that we can go beyond our mind.

581
00:54:06,000 --> 00:54:06,892

582
00:54:07,000 --> 00:54:09,892
If you don’t know how to go beyond mind,

583
00:54:10,000 --> 00:54:12,892
better sit down for your meditation, work it out.

584
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:15,892
With this mind all kinds of things will come.

585
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:22,892
Temper will come, intrigue will come, jealousies will come,

586
00:54:23,000 --> 00:54:33,892
all the six enemies that we have will come to us through this mind –

587
00:54:34,000 --> 00:54:39,892
means thinking, rationality. Everything can be rationalized.

588
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:43,892
“Why did you murder your wife?”

589
00:54:44,000 --> 00:54:46,892
"Because I hated her. She was this, she was that, she was that.”

590
00:54:47,000 --> 00:54:49,892
But you cannot murder her.

591
00:54:50,000 --> 00:54:53,892
“Why did you murder your husband?” “Because of this, because of that.”

592
00:54:54,000 --> 00:55:01,892
Because of this mind we start doing things which are absolutely wrong, which are sinful,

593
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:04,892
and then we try to rationalize it.

594
00:55:05,000 --> 00:55:10,892
Go against Agnya, go against reality,

595
00:55:11,000 --> 00:55:16,892
and then use your conditioning, use your, we can call,

596
00:55:17,000 --> 00:55:25,892
the ego to explain it, why you did it.

597
00:55:26,000 --> 00:55:30,892
All the time when we are doing like that we can never go beyond mind.

598
00:55:31,000 --> 00:55:36,892
We are so self-satisfied about ourselves. We think no end of ourselves.

599
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:45,892
Now, how are we to get out of it?

600
00:55:46,000 --> 00:55:48,892
Introspection.

601
00:55:49,000 --> 00:55:52,892
But it’s very difficult because people are afraid of themselves.

602
00:55:53,000 --> 00:55:57,892
They don’t want to introspect, because once they start introspecting they

603
00:55:58,000 --> 00:56:04,892
will know how sinful they have been, how wrong things they have been doing.

604
00:56:05,000 --> 00:56:10,892
And then they’ll hate themselves. So they don’t want to introspect.

605
00:56:11,000 --> 00:56:17,892
But it’s very important that we should introspect.

606
00:56:18,000 --> 00:56:29,892
That introspection is very helpful for you to overcome these two hurdles of your Agnya Chakra.

607
00:56:30,000 --> 00:56:31,892

608
00:56:32,000 --> 00:56:36,892
I’ve told you many a times: don’t argue with anybody

609
00:56:37,000 --> 00:56:41,892
because the other fellow, he is asking for argument is the one has lots of ego,

610
00:56:42,000 --> 00:56:46,892
and that ego is acting on you.

611
00:56:47,000 --> 00:56:55,892
So action/reaction starts, and we develop a habit of reacting to everything.

612
00:56:56,000 --> 00:57:00,892
Specially in the West, I have seen they react to everything, everything.

613
00:57:01,000 --> 00:57:04,892
For example, now, this thing is spread out here, now they have nothing to do.

614
00:57:05,000 --> 00:57:08,892
“But they could have had better, why is it so thin?”

615
00:57:09,000 --> 00:57:12,892
Well you pay for it now, you do it.

616
00:57:13,000 --> 00:57:15,892
They are walking across, they meet someone. "See, see this man.

617
00:57:16,000 --> 00:57:19,892
What sort of a person he is?”

618
00:57:20,000 --> 00:57:23,892
If there’s a beggar, then they’ll start criticizing.

619
00:57:24,000 --> 00:57:27,892
They'll criticize the government; they’ll criticize everyone.

620
00:57:28,000 --> 00:57:29,892
What about yourself?

621
00:57:30,000 --> 00:57:34,892
Instead of that why don’t you start doing something about it?

622
00:57:35,000 --> 00:57:40,892
If you can’t help it, if you are not going to do anything about it, why react?

623
00:57:41,000 --> 00:57:44,892
And this is the worst habit we have developed is to react,

624
00:57:45,000 --> 00:57:47,892
and we think we have every right to react.

625
00:57:48,000 --> 00:57:56,892
You have, but this right is self-destructive.

626
00:57:57,000 --> 00:58:01,892
To react on everything is not proper.

627
00:58:02,000 --> 00:58:06,892
You have no authority to react. It is to that extent.

628
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:11,892
You have to just witness, witness the whole thing.

629
00:58:12,000 --> 00:58:14,892
Once you start witnessing,

630
00:58:15,000 --> 00:58:21,892
you’ll be amazed that you will start seeing the play, play of the maya,

631
00:58:22,000 --> 00:58:26,892
as they call it, and you will see where you stand with it.

632
00:58:27,000 --> 00:58:31,892
Witnessing should be developed. All the time, witness.

633
00:58:32,000 --> 00:58:34,892
Am I witnessing?

634
00:58:35,000 --> 00:58:37,892
Many people say that I have very good memory

635
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:42,892
because I am all the time witnessing.

636
00:58:43,000 --> 00:58:47,892
Everything is recorded within Me like a picture.

637
00:58:48,000 --> 00:58:52,892
And then, when I have to say something, I have to correct something,

638
00:58:53,000 --> 00:58:57,892
all that I have witnessed comes to help Me.

639
00:58:58,000 --> 00:58:59,892

640
00:59:00,000 --> 00:59:05,892
First of all, we should not react, react to anything.

641
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:10,892
Some people are attached, say, to money.

642
00:59:11,000 --> 00:59:13,892
They’ll react, they’ll not give any money,

643
00:59:14,000 --> 00:59:16,892
they’ll keep all the money with themselves.

644
00:59:17,000 --> 00:59:20,892
In Sahaja Yoga also it happens.

645
00:59:21,000 --> 00:59:24,892
I’ve seen people who are very, very miserly about money.

646
00:59:25,000 --> 00:59:28,892
Another ones are who try to please others,

647
00:59:29,000 --> 00:59:32,892
then they’ll waste their money on lavish things for nothing at all.

648
00:59:33,000 --> 00:59:35,892
There’s no need to waste.

649
00:59:36,000 --> 00:59:37,892

650
00:59:38,000 --> 00:59:46,892
Reaction can come through anything. Seeing something you can react

651
00:59:47,000 --> 00:59:51,892
and you become so engrossed with it that you don’t realize

652
00:59:52,000 --> 00:59:57,892
that you are wasting all your brain energy on nonsensical things.

653
00:59:58,000 --> 01:00:06,892
This reaction comes when you have lost complete sense of judgment.

654
01:00:07,000 --> 01:00:14,892
You don’t know what you are losing, what you are gaining by this kind of reaction.

655
01:00:15,000 --> 01:00:23,892
And this reaction is going to destroy your inner being completely,

656
01:00:24,000 --> 01:00:27,892
because all the time you are here and you are there, and you’re there, and you are there,

657
01:00:28,000 --> 01:00:30,892
and you are nowhere here.

658
01:00:31,000 --> 01:00:32,892

659
01:00:33,000 --> 01:00:39,892
If you are a very criticizing type of a person, try to stop it completely. Criticize yourself,

660
01:00:40,000 --> 01:00:44,892
direct that energy towards yourself. "Who am I to criticize others?

661
01:00:45,000 --> 01:00:48,892
Who am I to react to anything?

662
01:00:49,000 --> 01:00:58,892
”Put a challenge to yourself, and you will see that your ego will subside.

663
01:00:59,000 --> 01:01:02,892

664
01:01:03,000 --> 01:01:05,892
One day somebody came and told Me that

665
01:01:06,000 --> 01:01:10,892
“Mother I feel so angry, I feel like beating everyone.”

666
01:01:11,000 --> 01:01:16,892
I said, “All right, do one thing. Take a chappel and hit on your head. Finished.

667
01:01:17,000 --> 01:01:23,892
That’s the only way you can get rid of this habit that you want to beat others.”

668
01:01:24,000 --> 01:01:29,892
Didn’t like it much, but I think by that he is improved.

669
01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:30,892

670
01:01:31,000 --> 01:01:39,892
Now, conditioning also should be seen. “Am I a conditioned person?

671
01:01:40,000 --> 01:01:44,892
If my conditioning is there, then is it a good conditioning or a bad conditioning?

672
01:01:45,000 --> 01:01:47,892
“At least you should have good conditioning.

673
01:01:48,000 --> 01:01:49,892
But even that, to an extreme if you go,

674
01:01:50,000 --> 01:01:54,892
you can create a problem for yourself and for others.

675
01:01:55,000 --> 01:02:00,892
Most of these rituals and things started as a good conditioning.

676
01:02:01,000 --> 01:02:10,892
Then it became like a trap, and they could not get out of it.

677
01:02:11,000 --> 01:02:15,892
It’s a part and parcel of it, one has to accept.

678
01:02:16,000 --> 01:02:18,892
Then what should we do?

679
01:02:19,000 --> 01:02:27,892
We should not react. Just see the drama and you’ll be surprised,

680
01:02:28,000 --> 01:02:28,892

681
01:02:29,000 --> 01:02:35,892
without paying anything, without going to any theatre, every moment you can see the drama going on before you,

682
01:02:36,000 --> 01:02:42,892
which is so enjoyable, whether it is absurd, whether it is ridiculous,

683
01:02:43,000 --> 01:02:51,892
whether it is a sort of a - as you see in the films, you see, beating somebody and all that,

684
01:02:52,000 --> 01:02:58,892
you just see it and you do not react.

685
01:02:59,000 --> 01:03:06,892
Anything that you think is very perverse, ugly, immoral - don’t see, finished, gone.

686
01:03:07,000 --> 01:03:08,892

687
01:03:09,000 --> 01:03:14,892
So don’t tax your mind, because in the mind that we call it, so-called mind,

688
01:03:15,000 --> 01:03:26,892
it's actually the Agnya Chakra in the center of your optic chiasma.

689
01:03:27,000 --> 01:03:30,892
Just imagine. What a central place it has!

690
01:03:31,000 --> 01:03:35,892
And any disturbance to your Agnya, what it can do to your brain

691
01:03:36,000 --> 01:03:41,892
which is nothing but a lump of fat.

692
01:03:42,000 --> 01:03:43,892

693
01:03:44,000 --> 01:03:46,892
So how this Agnya can affect you,

694
01:03:47,000 --> 01:03:54,892
and how it works and creates perverted images, that is to be really seen.

695
01:03:55,000 --> 01:04:03,892
Conditionings, also you have seen, people are mentally so upset and so degenerated.

696
01:04:04,000 --> 01:04:05,892

697
01:04:06,000 --> 01:04:12,892
But the pure nature of Christ is innocence, you know that. He's Shri Ganesha.

698
01:04:13,000 --> 01:04:17,892
Shri Ganesha is an eternal Child.

699
01:04:18,000 --> 01:04:23,892
Christ is also complete innocence because He doesn’t react,

700
01:04:24,000 --> 01:04:26,892

701
01:04:27,000 --> 01:04:31,892
because He is not conditioned.

702
01:04:32,000 --> 01:04:35,892
Children are not conditioned so much as we are.

703
01:04:36,000 --> 01:04:37,892

704
01:04:38,000 --> 01:04:40,892
If you talk to children, if you speak to them,

705
01:04:41,000 --> 01:04:47,892
you’ll be amazed how innocent they are and how innocently they talk.

706
01:04:48,000 --> 01:04:55,892
Once My granddaughter asked Me, “What do You think of the poor children of the tiger?”

707
01:04:56,000 --> 01:04:57,892
I said, “Why?”

708
01:04:58,000 --> 01:05:06,892
“You know their father tells them that ‘You eat human beings,’ and what can they do?

709
01:05:07,000 --> 01:05:11,892
They have to eat human beings after all.” You see, so innocent.

710
01:05:12,000 --> 01:05:16,892
So I told her that they are under a complete control of God.

711
01:05:17,000 --> 01:05:21,892
Whatever they are doing, they are not going to be held responsible.

712
01:05:22,000 --> 01:05:24,892
It’s only for human beings

713
01:05:25,000 --> 01:05:33,892

714
01:05:34,000 --> 01:05:37,892
that God has given this freedom.

715
01:05:38,000 --> 01:05:44,892
It’s only human beings who can react in this manner.

716
01:05:45,000 --> 01:05:48,892
So for animals it is, they are pashus,

717
01:05:49,000 --> 01:05:54,892
means they are completely under the control of the God Almighty.

718
01:05:55,000 --> 01:05:59,892
So they are swabhavas, everything, a serpent will be a serpent,

719
01:06:00,000 --> 01:06:05,892
